$ Stellarium API: core.moveToAltAzi

`core.moveToAltAzi` looks at a pair of coordinates that are specified in the *horizontal coordinate system* (aka *topocentric coordinate system*).

code {
core.moveToAltAzi(
   altitude,  // → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API#stellarium-parameters-angle[angle] of altitude
   azimuth ,  // → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API#stellarium-parameters-angle[angle] of azimuth
   duration   // duration in seconds, default = 1
)
code }

Because `core.moveToAltAzi` is based on horizon of location of the observer, the same pair of coordinates does not look into the same direction on two different places.

{ Example

  gh|about-Stellarium|/API/core/moveToAltAzi.ssc||

  gh|about-Stellarium|/API/core/img/moveToAltAzi.png||


}

sa:

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/moveToRaDec[`core.moveToRaDec`], `core.moveToRaDec2000`

  A grid of the *horizontal coordinate system* is displayed with → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/GridLinesMgr/setFlagAzimuthalGrid[`GridLinesMgr.setFlagAzimuthalGrid(true)`].

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API
